@startuml UpdateOrderStatus
title Update Order Status Flow with Event Publishing

actor "Kitchen\nStaff" as Staff
participant "API\nGateway" as Gateway
participant "Order Status\nService" as OSS
participant "ActiveMQ\nBroker" as Queue
participant "Order\nService" as OS

Staff -> Gateway: POST /orders/{orderId}/status\n{status: "PREPARING", updatedBy: "kitchen"}
activate Gateway
Gateway -> OSS: Forward request
activate OSS

note over OSS
  1. Validate status transition
  2. Validate against item statuses
  3. Record new status
end note

OSS -> OSS: Validate & Record\nOrderStatusHistory

OSS -> Queue: PUBLISH OrderStatusChangedEvent\n(async, non-blocking)
activate Queue
Queue --> OSS: Published

OSS --> Gateway: HTTP 201 Created\nOrderStatusHistory{id, status, timestamp}
deactivate OSS
Gateway --> Staff: Response
deactivate Gateway

par Async Event Processing
  Queue -> OS: Message on topic:\norder-status-changed
  activate OS
  
  ' note over OS
  '   Event contains:
  '   - orderId
  '   - newStatus
  '   - oldStatus
  '   - eventId (idempotent)
  '   - timestamp
  ' end note
  
  OS -> OS: UPDATE Order.status\n= PREPARING
  OS --> Queue: Event consumed
  deactivate OS
end

deactivate Queue

' note over OSS, OS
'   If item status changes:
'   OrderItemStatusChangedEvent\npublished to order-item-status-changed topic
'   Order Service updates item status\n& recalculates totalPrice
' end note
@enduml
